 to have Dr. Rodriguez drive the initiatives and programs to cultivate a climate of diversity and equity in which individual students, faculty, and staff feel welcomed, valued for their contributions, and feel their identities can be openly expressed,” said Dr. Alex Stagnaro-Green, Dean of the University of Illinois College of Medicine at Rockford. “We are an academic medical center committed to developing an optimal learning environment for training healthcare professionals, conducting innovative research, and dedicated to improving the health and wellness of our society. Dr. Rodriguez’s experience and educational background make him an excellent addition to our faculty and we are excited to have him drive our efforts to recruit and retain faculty to improve and expand diversity and inclusion.” Additionally, Dr. Rodriguez will work with the Offices of Student and Academic Affairs in addressing issues of climate for diverse student populations. Dr. Rodriguez will continue his practice as a cosmetic and reconstructive plastic surgeon with OSF Cosmetic and Reconstructive Plastic Surgery in Rockford, Illinois. A graduate of Michigan State University College of Human Medicine, he completed his general surgical residency at SUMMA Health System in Akron, Ohio, followed by a plastic surgery fellowship at the University of Illinois at Chicago. Certified by the American Board of Plastic Surgery, Dr. Rodriguez has received numerous awards including the Faculty & Staff Aureus Award, the Excellence in Teaching Award, the Chicago Society of Plastic Surgeons Research Award, and numerous others. Education MD Admissions Rockford Interviews MD Curriculum Campus Specific Programs Curriculum by Year M1 Year M2 Year M3 and M4 Years Course Management/Blackboard Exams/Benware/Course Evaluations Visiting Students Medical Education and Evaluation MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Office Academic Skills Step 1 Resources Housing Computing Registrar Career Services Scholarship O